","377 kJ \/ 90 kcal","1 g","11 g","4.7 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["The Anzac biscuit is a sweet biscuit which is popular in Australia and New Zealand. The original biscuit was not sweet at all; rather it was a savory hardtack biscuit (also known as an Anzac tile or wafer) that was used in Australian and New Zealand Army Corps (ANZAC) soldiers’ rations as a substitute for bread in World War I.","Store cookies in an airtight container until ready to use.<br>- Golden syrup can be found in Cost Plus World Market and some Safeway stores."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","30m","30 pieces"]}